-- Occidental Petroleum Chief Irani Plans to Step Down in May, WSJ Reports
-- B y   J e r a n   W i t t e n s t e i n
-- 2010-10-14T02:50:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/occidental-petroleum-chief-irani-plans-to-step-down-in-may-wsj-reports.html
Occidental Petroleum Corp. Chief
Executive Officer Ray Irani plans to step down from the post in
May, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing the company.  Irani will remain in the role of chairman until the end of
2014 and receive a pay package reduction, the newspaper said.
Occidental may make the announcement as soon as tomorrow,
according to the report.  President Stephen I. Chazen will succeed Irani as chief
executive officer, the Journal said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jeran Wittenstein at 
 jwittenstei1@bloomberg.net  